long_desc.thetext: Sharing via Poster should be implemented for 1.1
Is there a spec/mock we can get attached to this bug? Thanks.

Created attachment 524662 Poster design spec
Attached design specification for the poster to this bug.
The designer would like this poster to print in landscape (it's been designed for a US 11in x 8.5in paper sheet).

L10n: 5 new strings have been created and pushed in this commit: https://github.com/mozilla/spark/commit/67d93ff1c68a214525c6fa82305ff27e55508ed9 New strings: - "Get Firefox on your Android" - "Firefox is available for Android phones (2.0 and above)
and the Nokia N900." - "Get Firefox on your Android" - "Get Firefox Home on your iPhone" - "Play Spark, share and earn badges"
The code is pushed but not testable until bug 649169 is resolved.

The new poster generation is now available for QA.
Log in with a user and click on "Create a poster" in the Share section of the logged-in homepage.
Commits: https://github.com/mozilla/spark/commit/67d93ff1c68a214525c6fa82305ff27e55508ed9 https://github.com/mozilla/spark/commit/bd1ae5331ebc4f5dab809a9e4841a8979ab57a88

Let me add that the Firefox logo is smaller in the real poster than in the design specification because the logo isn't publicly available in vector format.
To my knowledge, the image we're using is the highest resolution available (https://wiki.mozilla.org/Firefox3.5/Logos).
Increasing the size to match the design would result in poor output quality on paper.

I just noticed that the current URL of the QR code (at the bottom-left corner of the poster) is missing a parameter in the querystring to indicate that it's coming from a poster.
Re-opening because it won't award the "Street Team" badge.
